==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Habendum
<hw>Ha*ben"dum</hw> <pr>(h⟦adot⟧*b⟦ecr⟧n"d⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., that must be had.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>That part of a deed which follows the part called the
<xex>premises</xex>, and determines the extent of the interest or estate
granted; -- so called because it begins with the word
<ex>Habendum</ex>.</def> <rj><au>Kent.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haberdash</ent>⟦br⟧
